rich your family life, connect with your children, and celebrate your ancestors by learning to tell family stories, folktales, and nursery rhymes. Telling Tales: Storytelling in the Family is a fascinating guide to the art of gathering and telling stories. Written by three renowned storytellers, Telling Tales includes personal stories, how-to tips and extensive resource lists, and builds upon the success of the acclaimed first edition. Storytelling is contagious. Telling stories helps us make sense of what is happening around us and within ourselves. Stories are our powerful gift to the younger generation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArt de conter. 0aFamiliesvFolklore. 0aFamiliesxFolklore. 0aFamillexFolklore. 0aStorytelling. 7aFAMILY & RELATIONSHIPS / General.2bisacsh  aFolklore.  aLibrary Science.1 aHarris, Merle, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLottridge, Celia Barker, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aStotter, Ruth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978177212338840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781772123388423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781772123388/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles